content:
The RuneScape Wiki also has an article on: rsw:Sewers

Sewers are artificial, dungeon-like, underground tunnel networks through which waste is disposed of. In RuneScape, sewers are usually areas beneath large cities where monsters can be found. Sewers may refer to:

  • Ardougne Sewers, a small sewage network running beneath East and West Ardougne
  • Draynor Sewers, sewers beneath Draynor Village
  • Falador Sewers, a location visited in the novel Betrayal at Falador
  • Varrock Sewers, a large sewage network beneath Varrock, and by far the largest in RuneScape
  • Sewer valves, interactive scenery found south of East Ardougne
  • The Warrens, a sewer located beneath Port Piscarilius
 This page is used to distinguish between articles with similar names.

'''Sewers''' are artificial, [[dungeon]]-like, underground tunnel networks through which waste is disposed of. In ''[[RuneScape]]'', sewers are usually areas beneath large cities where [[monster]]s can be found. Sewers may refer to:

*[[Ardougne Sewers]], a small sewage network running beneath [[East Ardougne|East]] and [[West Ardougne]]
*[[Draynor Sewers]], sewers beneath [[Draynor Village]]
*[[rsw:Falador Sewers|Falador Sewers]], a location visited in the novel ''[[rsw:Betrayal at Falador|Betrayal at Falador]]''
*[[Varrock Sewers]], a large sewage network beneath [[Varrock]], and by far the largest in ''RuneScape''
*[[Sewer valve]]s, interactive scenery found south of [[East Ardougne]]
*[[The Warrens]], a sewer located beneath [[Port Piscarilius]]
